<bibRefCitation id="D74FCDF3A52BFFDF2C91F850FB8EF86D" author="Roewer, C. F." box="[938,1114,1969,1996]" pageId="16" pageNumber="72" pagination="751 - 782" refId="ref13685" refString="Roewer, C. F. (1955 a) Die Araneen der Osterreichischen Iran-Expedition 1949 / 50. Sitzungsberichte der Osterreichischen Akademie der Wissenschaften, Series I, 164, 751 - 782." type="journal article" year="1955">Roewer (1955a</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 11) corresponds well to 
<taxonomicName id="74DECB81A52BFFDF2FACF837FF2AF84E" baseAuthorityName="Mozaffarian &amp; Marusik" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[151,254,2005,2031]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Trochosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="81AA6C10A52BFFDF2FACF837FF2AF84E" box="[151,254,2005,2031]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="72">Trochosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Examination of the type revealed that the epigyne was inaccurately drawn (cf. 
<figureCitation id="2BE5AC87A52BFFDF2BB6F837FAB7F84E" box="[1165,1379,2005,2031]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1796,1820]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,815,1761]" captionTargetId="figure-202@15.[151,1435,811,1772]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 13. Holotype female of Pardosa persica (A–C) and Arctosa tbilisiensis females (D–G): holotypes of Trochosa impercussa (D–F) and T. afghana (G). A, D female habitus, dorsal; B, E photographs of epigyne, ventral; C, F–G original line figures of epigyne. C, F after Roewer (1955a) and G after Roewer (1960b)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4412791" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4412791/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="72">Figs. 13B and 13C</figureCitation>
) and that the 
<typeStatus id="6C650EA0A52AFFDE2FCFFF75FE82FF10" box="[244,342,151,177]" pageId="17" pageNumber="73">holotype</typeStatus>
female has a pattern typical to 
<emphasis id="81AA6C10A52AFFDE2D87FF75FC97FF10" box="[700,835,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="73">
<taxonomicName id="74DECB81A52AFFDE2D87FF75FCCEFF10" authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1847" baseAuthorityName="C. L. Koch" baseAuthorityYear="1847" box="[700,794,151,177]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Pardosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="lato">Pardosa</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9A99D16BA52AFFDE2C19FF75FC97FF10" box="[802,835,151,177]" pageId="17" pageNumber="73" sensu="lato">s.l.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
Judging from the epigyne, it may belong to the 
<taxonomicName id="74DECB81A52AFFDE2A52FF75FEECFF74" baseAuthorityName="Thorell" baseAuthorityYear="1872" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Pardosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nebulosa">
<emphasis id="81AA6C10A52AFFDE2A52FF75FEECFF74" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="73">Pardosa nebulosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group. This group was once considered a separate genus, 
<taxonomicName id="74DECB81A52AFFDE2CFFFF59FB1BFF74" authority="Simon, 1898" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1898" box="[964,1231,187,213]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Acroniops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="81AA6C10A52AFFDE2CFFFF59FBE2FF74" box="[964,1078,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="73">Acroniops</emphasis>
Simon, 1898
</taxonomicName>
, currently a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="74DECB81A52AFFDE2E18FF3DFD91FF58" authority="C. L. Koch, 1847" authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1847" baseAuthorityName="C. L. Koch" baseAuthorityYear="1847" box="[291,581,223,249]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Pardosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="81AA6C10A52AFFDE2E18FF3DFE55FF58" box="[291,385,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="73">Pardosa</emphasis>
C.L. 
<bibRefCitation id="D74FCDF3A52AFFDE2E84FF3DFD91FF58" author="Koch, C. L." box="[447,581,223,249]" pageId="17" pageNumber="73" pagination="541 - 563" refId="ref12075" refString="Koch, C. L. (1847) s. n. In: Die Arachniden. Vierzehnter Band, Funfzehnter Band, Sechszehnter und letzter Band &amp; Sechszehnter und letzter Band. J. L. Lotzbeck, Nurnberg, pp. 89 - 210 + pls. 481 - 504 (f. 1343 - 1412), pp. 1 - 136 + pls. 505 - 540 (f. 1413 - 1504) &amp; pp. 1 - 80 + pls. 541 - 563 (f. 1505 - 1550) + pp. 1 - 64 (Index)." type="book chapter" year="1847">Koch, 1847</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The new combination provided for Roewer’s species led to secondary homonymy with 
<taxonomicName id="74DECB81A52AFFDE2E1EFEE1FCA6FEBC" authority="Marusik, Ballarin &amp; Omelko, 2012" authorityName="Marusik, Ballarin &amp; Omelko" authorityYear="2012" box="[293,882,259,285]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Pardosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persica">
<emphasis id="81AA6C10A52AFFDE2E1EFEE1FE09FEBD" box="[293,477,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="73">Pardosa persica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="D74FCDF3A52AFFDE2EDFFEE1FCA6FEBC" author="Marusik, Y. M. &amp; Ballarin, F. &amp; Omelko, M. M." box="[484,882,259,285]" pageId="17" pageNumber="73" pagination="111 - 123" refId="ref12680" refString="Marusik, Y. M., Ballarin, F. &amp; Omelko, M. M. (2012) On the Pardosa monticola - species group from Iran (Araneae: Lycosidae). Zoology in the Middle East, 56, 111 - 123. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 09397140.2012.10648946" type="journal article" year="2012">Marusik, Ballarin &amp; Omelko, 2012</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, the species belonging to the 
<taxonomicName id="74DECB81A52AFFDE2B85FEE1FA47FEBC" baseAuthorityName="Clerck" baseAuthorityYear="1757" box="[1214,1427,259,285]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Pardosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monticola">
<emphasis id="81AA6C10A52AFFDE2B85FEE1FA47FEBC" box="[1214,1427,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="73">Pardosa monticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- group that was also once considered a separate genus, 
<taxonomicName id="74DECB81A52AFFDE2DC2FEC5FBC2FEE0" authority="Roewer, 1955" authorityName="Roewer" authorityYear="1955" box="[761,1046,294,321]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Pardosops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="81AA6C10A52AFFDE2DC2FEC5FCA4FEE0" box="[761,880,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="73">Pardosops</emphasis>
Roewer, 1955
</taxonomicName>
. In any case, we herein replace the secondary junior homonym with 
<taxonomicName id="74DECB81A52AFFDE2D30FEA9FD5CFEC5" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Nadolny" authorityYear="2020" box="[523,648,331,356]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Pardosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persiana" status="nom. n.">
<emphasis id="81AA6C10A52AFFDE2D30FEA9FD5CFEC5" box="[523,648,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="73">P. persiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="81AA6C10A52AFFDE2DB4FEA9FD3DFEC4" bold="true" box="[655,745,331,357]" pageId="17" pageNumber="73">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9A99D16BA52AFFDE2DB4FEA9FD3DFEC4" box="[655,745,331,357]" pageId="17" pageNumber="73">nom. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(pro 
<taxonomicName id="74DECB81A52AFFDE2C1DFEA9FAA6FEC4" authority="Marusik, Ballarin &amp; Omelko, 2012" authorityName="Marusik, Ballarin &amp; Omelko" authorityYear="2012" box="[806,1394,331,357]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Pardosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persica">
<emphasis id="81AA6C10A52AFFDE2C1DFEA9FC08FEC5" box="[806,988,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="73">Pardosa persica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="D74FCDF3A52AFFDE2CDFFEA9FAA6FEC4" author="Marusik, Y. M. &amp; Ballarin, F. &amp; Omelko, M. M." box="[996,1394,331,357]" pageId="17" pageNumber="73" pagination="111 - 123" refId="ref12680" refString="Marusik, Y. M., Ballarin, F. &amp; Omelko, M. M. (2012) On the Pardosa monticola - species group from Iran (Araneae: Lycosidae). Zoology in the Middle East, 56, 111 - 123. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 09397140.2012.10648946" type="journal article" year="2012">Marusik, Ballarin &amp; Omelko, 2012</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
